  <static seed="1428" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/complexFractions11.pg">
    <statement><p>Calculate the following. Use an improper fraction in your answer.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ 1 }{ \frac{7}{2} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{1}{7} }{2} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{2}{7}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{14}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p>We multiply <m>2</m> in both the numerator and denominator:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{ 1 }{ \frac{7}{2} } 
      \amp = \frac{ 1 \cdot 2 }{ \frac{7}{2} \cdot 2 } \\
      \amp = {{\frac{2}{7}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>We multiply <m>7</m> in both the numerator and denominator:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{ \frac{1}{7} }{2} 
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{1}{7} \cdot 7 }{ 2 \cdot 7 } \\
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{14}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</solution>
